   <h1> Ingredients:</h1>
   <ul>
<li>8 oz (225g) rice noodles (preferably flat)</li>
<li>2 tablespoons tamarind paste</li>
<li>3 tablespoons fish sauce</li>
<li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
<li>1 tablespoon brown sugar (or palm sugar)</li>
<li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
<li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
<li>1 shallot, finely chopped</li>
<li>2 eggs, lightly beaten</li>
<li>1 cup tofu, diced (optional)</li>
<li>1 cup shrimp, peeled and deveined (optional)</li>
<li>1 cup chicken breast, thinly sliced (optional)</li>
<li>1 cup bean sprouts</li>
<li>4 green onions, chopped</li>
<li>1/4 cup roasted peanuts, chopped</li>
<li>Lime wedges for serving</li>
<li>Fresh cilantro for garnish (optional)</li>
</ul>
<h1>Instructions:</h1>
 <h2>Prepare Rice Noodles:  </h2>
 <ul>
    <li> Soak the rice noodles in warm water for about 30 minutes, or until softened. Drain and set aside.</li>
 </ul>

<h2>Make Pad Thai Sauce:</h2>
<ul><li>In a small bowl, mix together tamarind paste, fish sauce, soy sauce, and brown sugar until well combined. Set aside.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Cook Protein: </h2>
<ul>
    <li> Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and chopped shallot, and saut√© until fragrant. If using tofu, shrimp, or chicken, add them to the skillet and cook until cooked through.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Add Eggs: </h2>
<ul><li>Push the protein to one side of the skillet and add the beaten eggs to the other side. Scramble the eggs until cooked, then mix them with the protein.</li></ul>
<h2>Stir-fry Noodles: </h2>
<ul><li>Add the softened rice noodles to the skillet along with the prepared Pad Thai sauce. Toss everything together until the noodles are well coated in the sauce and heated through.</li></ul>
<h2>Add Vegetables: </h2>
<ul><li>Add bean sprouts and chopped green onions to the skillet, and toss to combine. Cook for another 1-2 minutes until the bean sprouts are slightly softened.</li></ul>
<h2>Serve:</h2>
<ul><li>Transfer the Pad Thai to serving plates. Sprinkle chopped roasted peanuts over the top and garnish with fresh cilantro (if using). Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over the Pad Thai before eating.</li></ul>
<h2>Enjoy:</h2>
<ul><li> Serve the Pad Thai hot and enjoy the delicious flavors!</li></ul>

